> Also assuming the worst that this cylinder is getting ready to drop a valve 
> and I need the heads rebuilt....how can I test the bottom end of the 
> engine? I'm wondering if I could just get away with rings, a valve 
> job/rebuilt heads, seals and such and leave the bottom end alone. I don't 
> have the cash to do a full engine rebuild.

that will be a big question mark. If you end up pulling the motor, an
endplay measurement will give you a good indicator of the condition of
the bottom end. Only teardown and measure will actually give you a
definate answer. do you have any data on how many miles are on the
engine, this can help decide as well.

